      "kwargs": {
        "content": "Execution of process_rule `J09B` could not be completed because the SQLite database is currently unavailable.\n\nWhat I did:\n\n1. Retrieved the process definition for `J09B` and confirmed the required steps (copy `decision_table`, add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, joins with `EABLG`, `NET_MASTER`, `SALES_MASTER`, create CSV `J09B`, email to `meter.readings@evu.com`, then drop temp table).\n2. Tried to access the database:\n   - `get_db_schema()` → `Error no database connection`\n   - `run_sqlite_query(\"SELECT name FROM sqlite_master ...\")` → `Error no database connection`\n3. Tried an independent CSV export (`prepare_csv`) to verify whether any SQL could run → same database connection error.\n4. Determined this is a major, systemic issue (no SQL operation can run), so it’s not something I can work around from here.\n5. Escalated to support as required, via `send_mail`:\n   - Sent an automatic diagnostic email to `support@company.com` describing:\n     - The process ID: `J09B`\n     - That all SQL-dependent steps (table copy, joins, CSV export) fail with `\"Error no database connection\"`.\n\nCurrent status of process `J09B`:\n\n- Step 1 (make `J09B_temp` from `decision_table`) and all subsequent database-related steps are blocked by the DB connection error.\n- No temporary table was created, no joins were performed, no `J09B.csv` was generated.\n- Because the CSV could not be created, I also could not send the final data to `meter.readings@evu.com`.\n\nNext action:\n\n- This requires intervention on the database side. Once support restores the database connection for the `decision_table` SQLite DB, you can ask me again to run process `J09B`, and I’ll execute the steps end-to-end as defined.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
